53
00:10:59.609 --> 00:11:02.445
<i>and then there are
legendary bad days.</i>

54
00:11:03.905 --> 00:11:06.616
<i>This was shaping up
to be one of those.</i>

55
00:11:08.868 --> 00:11:11.704
<i>Whole damn planet
wanted a piece of me.</i>

56
00:11:13.581 --> 00:11:15.625
<i>Can't stay in the open.</i>

57
00:11:17.794 --> 00:11:20.004
<i>Can't risk another attack.</i>

58
00:11:37.647 --> 00:11:41.484
<i>It's always the punch you don't
see coming that puts you down.</i>

59
00:11:44.904 --> 00:11:46.781
<i>But why didn't I see it?</i>

60
00:11:47.156 --> 00:11:48.157
(GRUNTS)

61
00:11:48.658 --> 00:11:51.160
<i>Of course they were
gonna try to kill me.</i>

62
00:11:51.244 --> 00:11:53.788
<i>Death is what they do for a living.</i>

63
00:11:58.626 --> 00:12:01.254
<i>So the question ain't
"What happened?"</i>

64
00:12:01.337 --> 00:12:02.380
(STONE SHIFTING)

65
00:12:02.463 --> 00:12:03.548
(GROANS)

66
00:12:03.631 --> 00:12:07.218
<i>The question is
"What happened to me?"</i>

67
00:12:24.903 --> 00:12:26.070
(WOMAN MOANS)

68
00:12:30.450 --> 00:12:32.452
You are the Lord Marshal now.

69
00:12:33.870 --> 00:12:36.039
<i>How did they get so close?</i>

70
00:12:40.043 --> 00:12:43.046
<i>How did I let them
blindside me like that?</i>

71
00:12:44.047 --> 00:12:46.716
CROWD: Threshold!
Take us to the threshold!

72
00:12:47.383 --> 00:12:49.177
<i>RIDDICK:
Necromongers.</i>

73
00:12:50.345 --> 00:12:52.972
<i>Some wanted to put a
crown on my head.</i>

74
00:12:54.807 --> 00:12:57.685
<i>Some wanted to put a
noose around my neck.</i>

75
00:13:00.021 --> 00:13:03.066
Please. come back to bed.

76
00:13:04.651 --> 00:13:07.987
<i>Every Lord Marshal
was supposed to take some big oath.</i>

77
00:13:09.489 --> 00:13:14.035
<i>one that I never
really got around to.</i>

78
00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.623
<i>You could say it created
a little friction</i>

79
00:13:19.916 --> 00:13:22.502
<i>and more than a few assassins.</i>

80
00:13:25.505 --> 00:13:27.382
<i>I needed a way out.</i>

81
00:13:33.304 --> 00:13:35.223
<i>Some new place.</i>

82
00:13:37.141 --> 00:13:40.270
<i>Or maybe just an old one.</i>

83
00:13:40.562 --> 00:13:42.105
Furya.

84
00:13:42.647 --> 00:13:44.816
I know what it's called.

85
00:13:45.525 --> 00:13:47.610
You just don't know where it is.

86
00:13:48.111 --> 00:13:50.613
I need charts. I need maps.

87
00:13:50.697 --> 00:13:51.948
Impossible.
I need a direction.

88
00:13:52.031 --> 00:13:54.200
Purged from all records.
as you well know.

89
00:13:54.284 --> 00:13:58.079
But you remember where.
Commander Vaako.

90
00:13:59.539 --> 00:14:00.915
So many worlds...

91
00:14:02.792 --> 00:14:05.295
The only map left in existence

92
00:14:06.296 --> 00:14:10.216
is the one that's in
my head. Riddick.

93
00:14:16.222 --> 00:14:18.141
So what do you want?

94
00:14:21.811 --> 00:14:23.313
The crown?

95
00:14:28.484 --> 00:14:30.320
Transcendence.

96
00:14:34.657 --> 00:14:35.658
Krone.

97
00:14:36.826 --> 00:14:38.494
Break off a ship.

98
00:14:39.996 --> 00:14:41.831
Riddick's going home.

99
00:14:42.582 --> 00:14:44.000
<i>RIDDICK:
Vaako.</i>

100
00:14:47.170 --> 00:14:50.006
<i>You can't blame him
for dangling Furya.</i>

101
00:14:51.299 --> 00:14:53.343
<i>Home has a certain equity.</i>

102
00:14:56.596 --> 00:15:00.391
<i>But I do blame him
for what came next.</i>

103
00:15:15.323 --> 00:15:17.450
It's a long way to come.

104
00:15:18.284 --> 00:15:19.619
For this.

105
00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:24.374
<i>RIDDICK: This guy with
the fucked-up face. Krone.</i>

106
00:15:25.124 --> 00:15:27.835
<i>he was supposed to
be our ride home.</i>

107
00:15:29.921 --> 00:15:34.884
<i>But instead of Furya.
we wind up someplace called...</i>

108
00:15:34.968 --> 00:15:35.969
(SNIFFS)

109
00:15:36.052 --> 00:15:37.720
<i>Not Furya.</i>

110
00:15:46.813 --> 00:15:49.983
<i>Yet again. someone was
trying to play me.</i>

111
00:15:52.402 --> 00:15:53.861
<i>So yet again.</i>

112
00:15:56.447 --> 00:15:58.241
<i>we play for blood.</i>

113
