215
00:31:40.767 --> 00:31:42.560
Rain.
(GRUMBLING)

216
00:31:42.644 --> 00:31:44.395
It's a good thing.

217
00:31:45.438 --> 00:31:49.317
Just because you've never seen it
before doesn't mean it's a bad thing.

218
00:31:49.776 --> 00:31:51.527
Hey. easy.

219
00:32:06.292 --> 00:32:08.711
Looks like our time is up here.

220
00:32:13.258 --> 00:32:14.592
(WHIRRING)

221
00:33:31.836 --> 00:33:33.087
(PANTING)

222
00:33:58.279 --> 00:33:59.822
(WHIRRING STOPS)

223
00:34:07.705 --> 00:34:09.040
Nothing.

224
00:34:11.334 --> 00:34:13.169
Look again. Diaz.

225
00:34:16.839 --> 00:34:19.842
Somebody should teach
this Riddick asshole how to count.

226
00:34:20.176 --> 00:34:24.514
"Leave one ship"? Like we've got
a fucking spare laying around.

227
00:34:25.098 --> 00:34:26.683
Let's crank it up.

228
00:34:27.517 --> 00:34:28.518
(WHIRRING)

229
00:34:37.610 --> 00:34:39.696
Good morning. Cyclops.

230
00:34:54.544 --> 00:34:56.462
(SHIP POWERING DOWN)

231
00:35:03.636 --> 00:35:04.762
Hey. Luna.

232
00:35:07.640 --> 00:35:08.725
Yeah.

233
00:35:09.267 --> 00:35:10.643
Wake her up. kick her out of bed.

234
00:35:11.436 --> 00:35:12.896
What do you mean?

235
00:35:13.271 --> 00:35:14.898
We're running heavy.

236
00:35:15.231 --> 00:35:16.816
She's a prisoner.
Wasn't she gonna pay our way back?

237
00:35:16.900 --> 00:35:18.610
We're going big now.

238
00:35:18.985 --> 00:35:22.238
Okay? Cut that 60 kilos loose.

239
00:35:28.912 --> 00:35:29.913
(HISSING)

240
00:35:33.625 --> 00:35:34.626
(WHIRRS)

241
00:35:37.086 --> 00:35:38.296
(WHIRRS)

242
00:35:38.755 --> 00:35:40.256
Get away! Get away from me!

243
00:35:40.423 --> 00:35:41.883
Stop. just stop!

244
00:35:41.925 --> 00:35:43.593
What do you want now?

245
00:35:43.676 --> 00:35:46.429
I'm gonna take off the restraints.
Okay?

246
00:35:48.264 --> 00:35:49.515
I don't want them off.

247
00:35:49.599 --> 00:35:50.642
No. it's not like that.

248
00:35:51.643 --> 00:35:53.353
Nobody is gonna touch you now.

249
00:35:53.770 --> 00:35:55.605
Santana's head is
into other stuff now.

250
00:35:57.106 --> 00:35:58.691
Your lucky day.
(WHIRRS)

251
00:36:00.526 --> 00:36:01.527
(GROANS)

252
00:36:03.446 --> 00:36:04.447
(WHIRRS)

253
00:36:05.490 --> 00:36:06.824
Get the fuck away from me.

254
00:36:06.950 --> 00:36:08.284
Okay.

255
00:36:09.452 --> 00:36:11.454
What planet is this? Where are we?

256
00:36:11.496 --> 00:36:13.122
It's got air and water.
That's all you've got to know.

257
00:36:18.169 --> 00:36:19.337
But how am I supposed to survive...

258
00:36:19.420 --> 00:36:20.463
Just go.

259
00:36:21.464 --> 00:36:22.966
Before he changes his mind.

260
00:36:28.972 --> 00:36:30.306
(PANTING)

261
00:36:35.562 --> 00:36:36.563
(GRUNTS)

262
00:36:37.814 --> 00:36:39.315
(GUNSHOT)
(GROANS)

263
00:36:48.825 --> 00:36:51.119
I was getting attached to her.

264
00:36:53.746 --> 00:36:55.790
Now where is my box at?

265
00:37:01.671 --> 00:37:02.672
(GASPING)

266
00:37:18.688 --> 00:37:21.733
The name is Santana!

267
00:37:22.942 --> 00:37:25.695
Shot-caller for this
crew right here!

268
00:37:26.988 --> 00:37:29.407
I am the guy who knows all.

